Darleen R. SCHUSTER, Plaintiff-Appellant, Richard Allen Culbertson, Petitioner-Appellant,
v.
COMMISSIONER OF SOCIAL SECURITY, Defendant-Appellee. No. 16-14004 United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. MARCH 8, 2019 Richard Allen Culbertson, Sarah Fay, Culbertson Law Group, PLLC, Orlando, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellant Darleen R. Schuster. Richard Allen Culbertson, Culbertson Law Group, PLLC, Orlando, FL, for Petitioner-Appellant Richard Allen Culbertson. Rebecca Ringham, Jerome M. Albanese, Nadine DeLuca Elder, Megan Elizabeth Gideon, William Lawrence Hogan, Mary Ann Sloan, John C. Stoner, Susan Kelm Story, Richard Harrison Winters, Social Security Administration, Office of the General Counsel, Atlanta, GA, John F. Rudy, III, U.S. Attorney's Office, Tampa, FL, for Defendant-Appellee. Before MARTIN, JILL PRYOR, and ANDERSON, Circuit Judges.

ON REMAND FROM THE UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT

In light of the January 8, 2019 ruling of the Supreme Court in Culbertson v. Ber ryhill , 586 U.S. ----, 139 S.Ct. 517 , 201 L.Ed.2d 277 (2019), we REMAND this case to the District Court for calculation of attorney's fees.
